title: Google\Cloud\BigQuery\DataTransfer\V1\ListTransferRunsRequest
name: ListTransferRunsRequest
description:
A request to list data transfer runs. UI can use this method to show/filter specific data transfer runs. The data source can use this method to request all scheduled transfer runs.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.bigquery.datatransfer.v1.ListTransferRunsRequest

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.parent
params.description: Required. Name of transfer configuration for which transfer runs should be retrieved. Format of transfer configuration resource name is: projects/{project_id}/transferConfigs/{config_id} or projects/{project_id}/locations/{location_id}/transferConfigs/{config_id}.

params.name: data.states
params.description: When specified, only transfer runs with requested states are returned.

params.name: data.page_token
params.description: Pagination token, which can be used to request a specific page of ListTransferRunsRequest list results. For multiple-page results, ListTransferRunsResponse outputs a next_page token, which can be used as the page_token value to request the next page of list results.

params.name: data.page_size
params.description: Page size. The default page size is the maximum value of 1000 results.

params.name: data.run_attempt
params.description: Indicates how run attempts are to be pulled.
